        {
            "name": "User WebSocket",
            "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "description": "WebSocket endpoint for real-time channel subscriptions, threaded reply broadcasts, and WebRTC call signaling relays.\n\n### Usage flow:\n1. Connect to `ws://localhost:8000/ws/users/` (Auth is handled automatically via HttpOnly cookies)\n2. Subscribe to a workspace channel:\n   `{\n       \"type\": \"subscribe\",\n       \"channel_id\": 1\n   }`\n3. Post a real-time reply inside the channel:\n   `{\n       \"type\": \"new_reply\",\n       \"topic_id\": 1,\n       \"content\": \"Hello world!\"\n   }`\n4. Relaying WebRTC P2P Voice Call negotiation signals:\n   `{\n       \"type\": \"call_signal\",\n       \"receiver_id\": 2,\n       \"sdp\": \"OFFER\",\n       \"candidate\": {}\n   }`",
                "url": {
                    "raw": "ws://localhost:8000/ws/users/",
                    "protocol": "ws",
                    "host": [
                        "localhost"
                    ],
                    "port": "8000",
                    "path": [
                        "ws",
                        "users",
                        ""
                    ]
                }
            },
            "response": []
        }
